---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — The Narrow March">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">About</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 2rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-content">

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>The Modern Templar</h2>
          <blockquote class="about-quote">
            "He rides no horse. He carries no banner. He moves unseen — armored in prayer. Marching through cities of sin like salt through decay. A soldier not of empire — but of eternity."
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>Why "The Narrow March"</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Narrow</strong> — the narrow path (Matthew 7:14). Difficulty. Discipline. Separation from the wide road that leads to destruction.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>March</strong> — military movement. Daily steps. Sustained forward motion — not a sprint, but the long obedience in the same direction.
          </p>
          <p>
            Together: step after step after step. The narrow path doesn't walk itself.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
          <p>
            The Narrow March speaks to men who understand that faith is not passive. Men working on personal discipline and self-mastery.
            Men who are tired of soft, comfortable Christianity that demands nothing and changes no one.
          </p>
          <p>
            Whether you've drifted from the faith and are finding your way back, or you're seeking a faith that demands something of you —
            this is the place where iron sharpens iron. No shortcuts. No comfort theology. Just the Word of God and the daily discipline to live by it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>What We Believe</h2>
          <p>
            We hold to the historic Christian faith. Scripture alone is our authority. Salvation is by grace alone, through faith alone, in Christ alone,
            to the glory of God alone. We believe the Bible is the inerrant, inspired Word of God — profitable for teaching, reproof, correction,
            and training in righteousness.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>The Mission</h2>
          <p>
            We are not building an audience. We are forging soldiers. Every devotional, every sermon, every newsletter exists to accomplish one thing:
            to equip men to follow the Lamb — not into comfort, but into the fire.
          </p>
          <p>The war has never ended. Only the armor has changed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-cta">
          <a href="/daily-crusader" class="btn btn-primary">Start the Daily Crusader</a>
          <a href="/newsletter" class="btn btn-outline">Join the Newsletter</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-top: 7rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .about-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-block {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-block h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .about-block p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .about-cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>
